                            <comment id="14476617" author="carstenlenz" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2014 11:33:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I review this bug and it is more general: Comments after array elements but before the &apos;,&apos; or &apos;]&apos; currently throw exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I updated the existing unit test and created a fix for this that ignores comments before the &apos;,&apos; or &apos;]&apos; of the current array. &lt;br/&gt;
This is the pull request: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/pull/535&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/pull/535&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
